# GitHub Packages auth template for installing `@moraya/markdown-core` from the
# private GitHub Packages registry. Copy to ~/.npmrc (preferred) or to ./.npmrc
# (gitignored locally; do NOT commit a populated copy).
#
# Required scope on the GitHub PAT:
#   - read:packages
#
# Get a PAT at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Choose "Fine-grained" → "Selected repositories: zouwei/moraya-markdown-core"
# → Permissions: Repository → Contents: Read; Metadata: Read; Packages: Read.
#
# CI (GitHub Actions): use the workflow's GITHUB_TOKEN via setup-node's
# `registry-url: https://npm.pkg.github.com` + `scope: '@moraya'` inputs;
# do NOT echo a token into a checked-in file.
#
# Pre-publication bridge: until @moraya/markdown-core@0.1.0 is published, this
# repo consumes a vendored tarball at ./vendor/moraya-markdown-core-0.1.0.tgz
# and the registry config below has no effect. Once the registry-published
# version exists, switch the dependency to "^0.1.0" and rely on this .npmrc.

@moraya:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
